If, then, we may at last leave behind us the controversies which have gathered round this particular fragment of Virgil’s poetry, we come to a rather wider question. Do Virgil’s other writings show anything like the hope of a Messiah? and if so, what kind of a Messiah do they foreshadow? We . have seen that certain external coincid- ences with Christian tradition were merely accidental: is there beneath these any real harmony?
